EFTA has several free trade agreements with non-EU countries as well as declarations on cooperation and joint workgroups to improve trade. Currently, the EFTA States have established preferential trade relations with 24 states and territories, in addition to the 28 [[member states of the European Union]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.efta.int/free-trade.aspx |title=Free Trade &#124; European Free Trade Association |publisher=Efta.int |date=2014-09-16 |accessdate=2016-08-17}}</ref>

EFTA's interactive Free Trade Map gives an overview of the partners worldwide.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.efta.int/free-trade/fta-map |title=Free Trade Map &#124; European Free Trade Association |publisher=Efta.int |date= |accessdate=2016-08-17}}</ref>

